.TH Man_Page 1

.SH NAME
holbertonschool-simple_shell  aka SimShell \- a custom shell program that prompts and executes basic commands

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B SimShell
[echo]
[exit]
[ls]
[ls -l]
[ls -l -a]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B SimShell
The project's code consists of three C files (execmd.c, get_location.c, and main.c) and a header file (main.h). It is a simple implementation of a shell-like program that takes user input, parses the input into commands and arguments, and then executes the specified command using the execve system call.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP

.TP
.BR [echo]
Writes its arguemtns separated by blanks and terminated by a new line on the standard output.

.TP
.BR [exit]
Causes an immediate termination of the entire program done by the operation system.

.BR [ls]
Prints the lists of files in long listing format.

.TP
.BR [ls -l]
Shows every single thing located in the directory.

.TP
.BR [ls -l -a]
Shows all files listed in the directory even entries starting with '.'.

